abstract="Continuous growth of data and customer-focused business has derived a lot of changes in the existing software frameworks. Application development pattern is shifting towards designing of prediction frameworks. Business organizations are deploying predictive frameworks and predictive computing techniques to understand the behaviour of their customers, similarly, healthcare industry is using these predictive models to make predictions about the disease by using various data mining techniques over existing data from various patients. In this chapter, we have discussed the role of IoT and its applications in various sectors like health care, retail, transportation and industries. IoT helps in collection of data in real time and provides fast and effective prediction of information in respective sector. Researchers, data scientists and engineers have begun to design and develop models, and IoT-based computing systems to solve the major challenges using the predictive computing techniques. These major challenges are categorized as technical challenges, device lifetime energy challenges, representation of massive data challenge and incomplete data representation challenge. In IoT-based predictive computation, the predictive model performs the predictions of future observations. The prediction of data includes point-wise or interval-wise predictions, prediction regions or prediction analysis based on the distribution of data, and ranking method for new observations.",
