year="2019",
publisher="Springer International Publishing",
address="Cham",
pages="141--158",
abstract="Securing the volumes of data created by the Internet of Things is essential as IoT devices are increasingly used in health care, smarter cities, transportation systems, and more. The privacy of personal data, the safety of users, and the security of our infrastructure depend on it. There are already billions of IoT devices in use, and the numbers will continue to grow. Of the 13 billion data records breached across IT systems from 2013 through 2018, only 4{\%} were encrypted (https://breachlevelindex.com/). Pervasive encryption can protect data in transit and data at rest at multiple layers of the computing environment. It is a crucial strategy to enhance privacy and security in our increasingly connected world.",
isbn="978-3-030-15705-0",
doi="10.1007/978-3-030-15705-0_11",
url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-15705-0_11",
