abstract="Energy poverty is a term that is used for energy shortages in terms of providing electricity, heat, cold, etc. and it primarily means a limited or no access to these resources in the context of lack of necessary infrastructure, inability to connect to the transmission system, low income households etc. It is a problem that has a significant impact on the development and formation of young people. Quality of life is closely linked to housing and housing is determined by other factors, and energy poverty can be regarded as one of the most important factors. The aim of this paper is to name the energy poverty as an important determinant of the social dimension of housing quality, which may be a negative boundary element to the social exclusion of people.",
