abstract="In this chapter the topic of the delicate and complex relationship between food and the environment will be discussed, in the perspective of the achievement of a better quality of life for all the elements of nature. The dynamics of globalisation and the progressive individualisation of society are phenomena that, in different ways, lead to a greater desire for well-being, when the primary needs are achieved or exceeded. Human beings have acquired awareness about the fact that to satisfy this desire it is necessary to pursue a harmonious relationship with nature and landscape. Food and nutrition are directly involved in this search for balance between the need to obtain the nourishment for living and respect for the environmental dimension. In contemporary society nature is no longer considered a source to be exploited in order to satisfy human needs but a precious ally that allows improvement in the lives of all living beings with its resources.",
