abstract="This paper proposes a new cloud-based wheelchair assist system to support user mobility of impaired people. The smart wheelchair system is equipped with a pressure sensor cushion and accelerometer for posture detection, GPS for localization purposes, and accelerometer for wheelchair status monitoring. Moreover, impaired people are equipped with a body area network to better support user mobility and independence. Our non-invasive system collects accelerometer, pressure data, and GPS signals to recognize user's daily activities, to track his/her location and to monitor wheelchair status. The proposed system was prototyped using the BodyCloud middleware so as to allow caregivers real-time access to the information generated by the smart wheelchair system. Finally, a case study is proposed to show the effectiveness of the assist system in extracting useful information by using multi-sensor data fusion.",
